Package mmb

Interface GameObject

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Identifiable<java.lang.String>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Machine
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Player, SkeletalMachine, Universe
    public interface GameObject
extends Identifiable<java.lang.String>
    Author:
    oskar This interface is used for all game objects which can be:
    • called by their ID
    • identified online
    • assigned to a owner
    Following classes are game objects: (variables are placed in square brackets)
    • players - [nick]
    • machines: [English title]:[map]@[world]:[x],[y]
    • world behaviors: [title]:[world]
    • map behaviors: [title]:[map]@[world]
    • creatures: [title] #[UUID]
    • packets: packet #[UUID]
    • maps: map [map]@[world]
    • worlds: world [world]
    • tasks: task [taskID]
    • null objects: null
    • servers: [URL or IP address]

      • getOwner

        @Nullable
GameObject getOwner()
        Get the GameObject which owns this GameObject. If this is a top level GameObject, return null. The ownership is different from containment, which can be retrieved by #getContainer()
        If object is owned by a player, it returns a player. If object is public, it returns a server, or null if in local mode
        Returns:
        this GameObject's owner
